genresAdvancedInfo.name: houston indie
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Houston indie is a subgenre of indie rock that emerged in the 2000s. It is characterized by its DIY ethos and raw, unpolished sound. Houston indie bands often draw inspiration from the city's diverse musical heritage, incorporating elements of blues, country, and hip-hop into their music.
